          {
            "question": "Which AI video model is the best?",
            "answer": "It depends on your needs. Seedance 2.0 excels at cinematic video with audio and lip sync. Wan 2.7 offers the most versatile multi-modal input. Kling 3.0 is great for native audio video. Sora 2 Pro supports the longest duration (25s) with storyboard. HappyHorse 1.0 is the best open-source option, ranked #1 on Artificial Analysis."
          },
          {
            "question": "Which AI video model is the cheapest?",
            "answer": "Sora 2 offers the best value at 30 credits ($0.15) for a 10-second video. Hailuo 02 is also very affordable at 9.5 credits ($0.048) per second for 1080p. HappyHorse 1.0 is open-source and free to use."
          },
          {
            "question": "Which AI video model has the highest resolution?",
            "answer": "Most models support up to 1080p output. Seedance 2.0 currently supports up to 720p but offers advanced features like lip sync and multi-shot. Wan 2.7, Kling 3.0, Sora 2 Pro, Veo 3.1, and Hailuo 2.3 all support 1080p."
          },
          {
            "question": "Can I try these AI video models for free?",
            "answer": "Yes! All models on our platform offer free sign-up credits. You can test every model before committing to a paid plan."
          },
          {
            "question": "Which model supports the longest video duration?",
            "answer": "Sora 2 Pro Storyboard supports up to 25 seconds of multi-scene video. Seedance 2.0, Wan 2.6, Kling 3.0, and HappyHorse 1.0 support up to 15 seconds."
